replies.body:
A ping indicator would be great, I have seen this suggestion several times and have upvoted them all, since I'm one of those who has a lot connection problems.

Games are hosted by Riot's server (client-server), not peer-to-peer. Although, you can't directly ping the game's server, you can try using this IP (203.50.11.97) to check latency for Oceania instead. This IP is not official by any means, this is the IP that [LolReplay2](http://beta.leaguereplays.com/) uses to check latency.

{{champion:17}}
